<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="543" pageId="1" pageNumber="541" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1615,2036]" box="[151,499,1615,1640]" pageId="1" pageNumber="541">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1615,1640]" pageId="1" pageNumber="541">Description.</emphasis>
Male and female.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1615,2036]" pageId="1" pageNumber="541">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1651,1676]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="541">Head</emphasis>
. First flagellomere cream yellow in basal 
<number box="[744,754,1652,1676]" pageId="1" pageNumber="541" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[765,779,1652,1676]" pageId="1" pageNumber="541" value="3.0">3</number>
and yellowish brown in apical 
<number box="[1141,1156,1652,1676]" pageId="1" pageNumber="541" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[1166,1179,1652,1676]" pageId="1" pageNumber="541" value="3.0">3</number>
; palpus cream yellow; labella yellow. Gena 
<number box="[387,498,1688,1712]" pageId="1" pageNumber="541" value="0.1" valueMax="0.11" valueMin="0.09">0.09‒0.11</number>
of eye height.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1615,2036]" box="[199,1172,1723,1748]" pageId="1" pageNumber="541">
<emphasis box="[199,280,1723,1748]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="541">Thorax</emphasis>
. Anterior and posterior spiracles yellow. Two‒three postsutural intra-alar setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1615,2036]" pageId="1" pageNumber="541">
<emphasis box="[199,305,1759,1784]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="541">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Whitish yellow in ground color with blackish brown pruinosity medially. Male 
<number box="[1241,1254,1759,1784]" pageId="1" pageNumber="541" value="5.0">5</number>
th sternite (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1883,1906]" captionTargetBox="[191,1389,219,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[187,1389,195,1862]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Male 5 th sternite and terminalia of Cephalispa kudoi sp. nov.: 1. Male 5 th sternite in ventral view (setae omitted on the left side). 2. Same in lateral view (setae omitted). 3. Epandrium, surstylus and cerci in lateral view. 4. Same in dorsal view (setae omitted on the left side). 5. Hypandrium, postgonite and phallus in lateral view. 6. Distiphallus in dorsal view. (Abbreviations: cerc: cerci; epand: epandrium; hypand: hypandrium; pgt: postgonite; ph: phallus; sur: surstylus). (Scale bars = 0.2 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262975/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="541">
Figs 
<number box="[151,193,1796,1820]" pageId="1" pageNumber="541" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1‒2</number>
</figureCitation>
) nearly rectangular in ventral view, round and curved ventrally at posterior apex in lateral view with large ridge internally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1615,2036]" pageId="1" pageNumber="541">
<emphasis box="[199,381,1867,1892]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="541">Male terminalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[397,500,1867,1892]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1883,1906]" captionTargetBox="[191,1389,219,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[187,1389,195,1862]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Male 5 th sternite and terminalia of Cephalispa kudoi sp. nov.: 1. Male 5 th sternite in ventral view (setae omitted on the left side). 2. Same in lateral view (setae omitted). 3. Epandrium, surstylus and cerci in lateral view. 4. Same in dorsal view (setae omitted on the left side). 5. Hypandrium, postgonite and phallus in lateral view. 6. Distiphallus in dorsal view. (Abbreviations: cerc: cerci; epand: epandrium; hypand: hypandrium; pgt: postgonite; ph: phallus; sur: surstylus). (Scale bars = 0.2 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262975/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="541">
Figs 
<number box="[454,500,1867,1892]" pageId="1" pageNumber="541" value="4.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.0">3‒6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Surstylus nearly straight and pointed apically with some setae on entire length in lateral view, slightly narrow at middle in dorsal view; bacilliform sclerite strongly reduced; hypandrium nearly triangular in lateral view; postgonite broad, curved ventrally at middle and pointed at apex; phallus nearly straight, strongly notched at middle, hook-like apically in lateral view, asymmetric at apical half with membranous area in dorsal view.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262975/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="542" targetBox="[191,1389,219,1837]" targetPageId="2">
